# PromptEnhance Environment Variables

# ==============================================================================
# OPTIONAL: OpenAI API (for embeddings)
# ==============================================================================
# If not provided, the app will use mock embeddings (works fine for testing)
# Get your API key from: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...

# ==============================================================================
# OPTIONAL: Project Path
# ==============================================================================
# Override the default project path
# Default: current working directory
# PROJECT_PATH=/path/to/your/project

# ==============================================================================
# OPTIONAL: ChromaDB Configuration
# ==============================================================================
# Option 1: Local ChromaDB Server (runs in-memory by default)
# CHROMA_SERVER_URL=http://localhost:8000

# Option 2: ChromaDB Cloud (Recommended for production)
# Get your credentials from: https://trychroma.com/signup
# CHROMA_SERVER_URL=https://api.trychroma.com
# CHROMA_AUTH_TOKEN=your-chroma-cloud-token-here
# CHROMA_TENANT=default_tenant
# CHROMA_DATABASE=default_database

# ==============================================================================
# OPTIONAL: Debug Mode
# ==============================================================================
# Enable debug logging
# DEBUG=promptenhance:*

# ==============================================================================
# NOTES:
# ==============================================================================
#
# 1. FOR LOCAL DEVELOPMENT (No API Key Needed):
#    - Just run `npm install && npm run build`
#    - Use mock embeddings (free, works offline)
#    - Perfect for testing
#
# 2. FOR PRODUCTION (With Better Embeddings):
#    - Set OPENAI_API_KEY
#    - Embeddings cost ~$0.0001 per 1000 tokens (very cheap)
#    - Better semantic search quality
#
# 3. CHROMADB:
#    - By default, runs in-memory (no setup)
#    - Data cleared on restart
#    - For persistence, install ChromaDB server:
#      pip install chromadb
#      chroma run --path ./chroma_data
#
# 4. SECURITY:
#    - Never commit .env file to git
#    - .env is already in .gitignore
#    - Rotate API keys regularly
